Pure methanol-fueled engines can present challenges in cold weather, particularly in terms of starting and operational efficiency. To address these issues, a common solution is the use of a fuel mixture known as M85, which consists of 85% methanol and 15% gasoline. The inclusion of gasoline facilitates engine starting at lower temperatures.
